    • createCreditNote

      public CreditNote createCreditNote(CreditNoteRequest creditNoteRequest) throws ApiException
      Create credit note This endpoint is used to send a credit note to the Tax Service Adapter. A credit note is used to reduce the amount due on an invoice. If the credit note is issued after payments have been made for the invoice, refunds can be issued to the Customer.

      Returns:

    • voidCreditNote

      public void voidCreditNote(String creditNoteId, String invoiceId) throws ApiException
      Void credit note This endpoint is used to void the credit note for a specific credit note id. Voiding reverses the credit note, thereby restoring the amount due on the invoice.
      Parameters:
      creditNoteId - The unique identifier of the credit note at the Tax Service Adapter or Tax Service Provider. (required)
      invoiceId - The unique identifier of the invoice at the Tax Service Adapter or Tax Service Provider. (optional)
